        <h2 id="what-is-included">What Should Be Included in Any Website Quote</h2>
        <p>
          Regardless of which tier applies to your business, a professional website quote from a credible agency in Ahmedabad should clearly list the following. If any of these are missing, ask specifically before proceeding.
        </p>

        <div class="checklist-box">
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>Number of pages and a clear list of which pages are included</li>
            <li>Whether the design is custom or template-based (be specific about which template if the latter)</li>
            <li>Mobile responsiveness confirmation</li>
            <li>On-page SEO setup: meta titles, descriptions, heading structure, image alt text</li>
            <li>Number of revision rounds included and what counts as a revision</li>
            <li>Browser compatibility testing (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)</li>
            <li>Contact form setup and delivery destination</li>
            <li>Google Analytics installation</li>
            <li>Domain and hosting for the first year, or clear instructions if excluded</li>
            <li>Timeline with milestone dates, not just a final delivery date</li>
            <li>What happens after delivery: support period, bug fixes, maintenance options</li>
            <li>Payment terms: how much upfront, when the balance is due</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p>
          Any quote that does not specify these points is leaving room for disagreement later. The most common disputes between Ahmedabad clients and web agencies arise from exactly these gaps: the client assumed revisions were unlimited, the agency assumed domain was excluded, the client expected SEO setup, the agency did none.
        </p>


        <h2 id="hidden-costs">The Hidden Costs Most Agencies in Ahmedabad Do Not Mention</h2>
        <p>
          The quoted price for a website is rarely the total cost of ownership. These additional expenses are legitimate and expected, but you should budget for them from the start rather than encounter them as surprises.
        </p>

        <h3 id="domain-hosting">Domain and Hosting</h3>
        <p>
          A .com domain runs approximately ₹700 to ₹1,200 per year. A .in domain is around ₹500 to ₹800 per year. Shared hosting for a standard business website costs ₹3,000 to ₹8,000 per year from reputable providers. VPS hosting, which gives better performance for higher-traffic or e-commerce sites, starts around ₹5,000 to ₹15,000 per year. Many agencies include the first year of domain and shared hosting in their quote. Year two onward, this becomes your recurring cost.
        </p>

        <h3 id="ssl-certificate">SSL Certificate</h3>
        <p>
          An SSL certificate (the padlock in the address bar, making your URL https rather than http) is essential for trust and for Google rankings. Free SSL through Let's Encrypt is standard with most hosting providers today. If an agency quotes you extra for SSL, question it carefully.
        </p>

        <h3 id="content-creation">Content and Photography</h3>
        <p>
          A website is only as good as the content on it. If you are providing your own text and photos, budget time for it. If the agency is writing your content, expect to add ₹5,000 to ₹20,000 depending on the number of pages and depth required. Professional photography for your team, office, or products typically runs ₹8,000 to ₹25,000 for a half-day shoot in Ahmedabad. Stock photography is an alternative but creates generic-looking pages that undermine trust.
        </p>

        <h3 id="maintenance-cost">Ongoing Maintenance</h3>
        <p>
          Websites are not fire-and-forget. Plugins need updating, security patches need applying, broken links need fixing, and content needs refreshing. A monthly maintenance retainer from a reliable agency runs ₹2,000 to ₹8,000 per month. If you choose not to pay for maintenance, plan to spend time handling it yourself or accept a site that degrades in performance and security over time.
        </p>

        <h3 id="seo-costs">SEO and Marketing After Launch</h3>
        <p>
          A website that no one can find does not generate leads. Monthly SEO services in Ahmedabad start around ₹8,000 to ₹15,000 per month for basic local SEO. Comprehensive SEO campaigns with content creation run ₹20,000 to ₹50,000 per month. Google Ads management typically starts at ₹8,000 to ₹15,000 per month in management fees, separate from your actual ad budget.
        </p>


        <h2 id="red-flags">Red Flags in a Website Quote</h2>
        <p>
          After reviewing dozens of competitor quotes that clients have brought to us, these are the patterns that indicate you should ask very hard questions or walk away entirely.
        </p>

        <h3 id="red-flag-pricing">Extremely Low Prices Without Explanation</h3>
        <p>
          A "20-page custom website" for ₹8,000 to ₹12,000 is mathematically impossible if the agency is doing any real design work. At minimum rates, a skilled designer or developer in Ahmedabad costs ₹300 to ₹600 per hour. A proper 20-page custom website requires 80 to 150 hours of work. If the quote does not add up arithmetically, the agency is either using a cheap template and calling it custom, or they will make up the difference through scope restrictions later.
        </p>

        <h3 id="red-flag-payment">Full Payment Required Upfront</h3>
        <p>
          Legitimate agencies work on milestone-based payments: typically 40 to 50% upfront, 30 to 40% at a defined midpoint (such as design approval), and 10 to 20% on final delivery. Any agency asking for 100% payment before any work begins has no financial accountability for delivering what was promised. This is the single most common pattern in Ahmedabad web design fraud cases.
        </p>

        <h3 id="red-flag-vague">Vague or Verbal Scope</h3>
        <p>
          If the scope of work is not in writing, it does not exist. "We will build you a good website" is not a contract. Insist on a written proposal that lists every deliverable. If an agency resists putting specifics in writing, that tells you everything you need to know about how disputes will be handled later.
        </p>

        <h3 id="red-flag-noportfolio">No Portfolio or All Portfolio Sites Are Inaccessible</h3>
        <p>
          Every web agency should have a working portfolio of live sites you can visit and evaluate on your own phone. If the portfolio links are broken, if the sites look like the same template with different colours, or if no portfolio is offered at all, do not proceed.
        </p>


        <h2 id="evaluate-proposal">How to Evaluate and Compare Website Proposals</h2>
        <p>
          When comparing proposals from multiple Ahmedabad agencies, do not compare price. Compare value. Here is a practical framework:
        </p>
        <p>
          First, list out every deliverable each agency has specified and compare them side by side. A ₹30,000 quote that includes SEO setup, schema markup, Google Analytics, 2 rounds of revisions, and 6 months of support is genuinely cheaper than a ₹20,000 quote that includes none of those things, because you will be paying for them separately later.
        </p>
        <p>
          Second, check the portfolio against your own standard. Open their past work on your phone. Does it load quickly? Does the mobile menu work? Does it look professional in 2025 or like it was built in 2018?
        </p>
        <p>
          Third, assess the discovery process. An agency that asks detailed questions about your business goals, your customers, your competitors, and your existing marketing before quoting is taking your project seriously. An agency that asks only "how many pages?" and quotes immediately is treating you as a transaction.
        </p>
        <p>
          Fourth, ask specifically: What happens if I need a change after delivery? What is the support period? Who will be my main contact? How will you communicate project progress? The answers reveal the working relationship you will actually have, not the one described in the sales pitch.
        </p>


        <h2 id="dct-pricing">How DC Technolabs Prices Website Projects</h2>
        <p>
          We believe in full transparency because we have seen what happens when pricing is opaque. Here is how we structure our engagements:
        </p>
        <p>
          Our business websites start from ₹25,000 and include custom or semi-custom design, up to 12 pages, mobile-first responsive layout, on-page SEO setup, schema markup, Google Analytics and Search Console integration, a contact form, and 30 days of post-launch support. We do not quote ₹10,000 to start a conversation and reveal the real number after you are invested.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every project begins with a discovery call where we ask about your goals, your customers, and your competition before recommending anything. We send a written proposal with itemised deliverables. Payment is milestone-based: 40% upfront, 40% at design approval, 20% on launch. We do not ask for full payment before starting.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you want to see what we have built, our portfolio page shows live sites across industries including real estate, healthcare, manufacturing, retail, and professional services.
        </p>


        <h2 id="what-to-pay">What You Should Actually Pay in 2025</h2>
        <p>
          Based on the current Ahmedabad market and what different tiers genuinely deliver, here is an honest summary:
        </p>

        <div class="pricing-table-wrapper">
          <table class="pricing-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Website Type</th>
                <th>Realistic Price Range</th>
                <th>Best For</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Basic informational (5-8 pages)</td>
                <td>₹12,000 to ₹25,000</td>
                <td>New businesses, credibility pages</td>
              </tr>
