        <p>
          Any quote significantly below these ranges for the corresponding scope deserves a very specific explanation. Any quote significantly above these ranges should be backed by an equally specific justification of what additional value you are receiving.
        </p>


        <h2 id="questions-to-ask">Questions to Ask Any Agency Before Signing</h2>
        <p>
          Before committing to any web design agency in Ahmedabad, ask these questions and pay close attention to how clearly they answer:
        </p>
        <ol class="numbered-list">
          <li>Can I see 3 live websites you have built in the last 12 months for businesses similar to mine?</li>
          <li>Will the design be custom or template-based? If template-based, which template?</li>
          <li>What exactly is included in this quote? Please list every deliverable in writing.</li>
          <li>What is your payment structure? I will not pay more than 50% upfront.</li>
          <li>What happens if I want a change after you deliver the site?</li>
          <li>Who specifically will be building my website, and what is their experience?</li>
          <li>What does your timeline look like, and what are the milestone dates?</li>
          <li>What support is available after launch, and for how long?</li>
          <li>Does this quote include domain, hosting, and SSL, or are those separate?</li>
          <li>Have you built websites for businesses in my industry before?</li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          An agency that answers these clearly and without hesitation is worth working with. An agency that becomes vague, redirects the conversation, or pressures you to commit before answering is not.
        </p>


        <h2 id="bottom-line">The Bottom Line</h2>
        <p>
          Website pricing in Ahmedabad is chaotic because transparency is rare. Most agencies prefer to compete on headline price and reveal the real situation after you have committed. This creates a market where businesses routinely get less than they paid for, or pay significantly more than originally quoted once scope is added back in.
        </p>
        <p>
          The best investment you can make is not finding the cheapest quote. It is finding an agency that asks the right questions before quoting, puts everything in writing, operates on milestone payments, and can show you a portfolio of sites that actually look and perform the way yours needs to.
        </p>
        <p>
